Statement of Qualifications

1. Education and Experience in Transportation Policy and Planning

I hold a Ph.D. in Geography from Kent State University and a Master of Arts in Geography from SUNY Binghamton, with academic training in transportation planning, GIS, spatial analysis, and quantitative modeling.

As a Sustainability Transportation Analyst with Caltrans’ Director’s Office of Sustainability, I develop analytical methodologies and decision-support tools that support implementation of the Caltrans Strategic Management Plan, CAPTI, and statewide equity and sustainability initiatives.

My recent work includes leading the development of the EQI Maintenance Use Case, where I designed the analytical methodology, conducted statewide implementation analyses, and produced technical recommendations that integrate transportation equity into maintenance planning and resource allocation. I also support broader implementation of the Transportation Equity Index (EQI) by developing use cases, technical guidance, and analytical products that promote consistent application across Caltrans.

I currently lead the technical development of a Speed Performance research initiative, creating a data-driven analytical framework to identify excessive speeding and support future speed abatement planning, aligned with the Caltrans Strategic Management Plan. In addition, I developed the analytical methodology and technical documentation for the Corridor Prioritization Tool, providing a standardized decision-support framework aligned with the Caltrans Strategic Management Plan and CAPTI to support corridor planning and investment prioritization.

These experiences have strengthened my ability to translate transportation policy objectives into practical planning methodologies that support data-driven decision-making across Caltrans.

