2. Education and Experience with Data Analysis in the Transportation Field, Including GIS and Statistical Software

I have over ten years of experience applying GIS, spatial statistics, programming, and quantitative analysis to transportation planning. I am proficient in ArcGIS Pro, R, Python, SQL, and Tableau and routinely integrate transportation, demographic, and spatial datasets to support statewide planning initiatives.

At Caltrans, I independently develop analytical workflows that combine GIS and statistical methods into repeatable methodologies. My work includes processing large transportation datasets, automating analyses in R, developing performance metrics, and producing maps, dashboards, and technical reports for decision-makers.

For the EQI Maintenance Use Case, I developed a complete GIS and R workflow integrating maintenance records, EQI data, demographic information, and operational performance metrics. For the Speed Performance initiative, I developed statewide analytical methods to identify excessive speeding using traffic performance data and created standardized metrics to support future planning efforts. I also developed reusable analytical workflows and documentation that improve consistency, efficiency, and knowledge sharing within the Transportation Analysis Branch.

