3. Experience with Effective Communication Skills

My work requires regular collaboration with planners, engineers, GIS specialists, managers, and staff from multiple Caltrans divisions. I communicate through email, Microsoft Teams, WebEx, phone calls, in-person meetings, technical reports, presentations, and user documentation.

I regularly present analytical methodologies, discuss technical approaches, incorporate stakeholder feedback, and communicate findings to both technical and non-technical audiences. I authored technical documentation for the Corridor Prioritization Tool, contributed to EQI user guidance and implementation materials, and participated in Traffic Mobility Insight workshops evaluating AI-enabled transportation analysis tools.

These experiences have strengthened my ability to explain complex analytical concepts clearly, collaborate across multidisciplinary teams, and support transportation planning through effective communication and technical leadership.
